                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "4. In Chrome, it's rather hard to read Chinese characters with a lot of (horizontal) strokes. (see the screenshot attached)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Adjusting the UI font size per locale doesn't work because English Chrome users can visit Chinese pages. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "It seems that the font size for the tab title on Linux is smaller than that on Windows. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Changing the size for all categories in the Gnome appearance | fonts doesn't make any difference as if it's hard-coded. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " The UI font size of Firefox 3 gets larger when I increase the font size in Gnome apperaance | fonts. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If there's a bug filed on Chrome's UI fonts not dependent on the desktop setting (I'm aware of the one about anti-aliasing), this should be made dependent on that bug.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/jshin@chromium.org/", 
